args: Oh, my! A party? And this is all for me?\nThank you! I'm so happy!
Mommy said we have to give you a big\nparty 'cause you're the mayor's daughter!
H-hey now, stop all that talk!\nHa ha! Oh, I'm sorry, Catherine.\nShe does love to make up stories!
This is for you, Catherine!\nDad said to give it to you and tell you to\nplease do your shopping at his shop!
(What an awful dream. I can't believe\nit's already my birthday again...)
(The rich daughter of the mayor...\nI never want to be viewed through that\nlens again.)
(It's fine. I'm no longer simply ＂the\nmayor's daughter.＂ I'm a perfect woman\nwho's exceedingly capable!)
Good morning. Er, where is Father?
He left for Saint Lotier, but should\nreturn within the week.
Speaking of the master, he left a\nbirthday present for you in my care.
I see. Please put it in my room.
(I suppose Father won't be wishing me a\nhappy birthday in person this year, either.)
Pheeew! It's finally over...\nMy brain is absolute mush...\nI'm going to collapse...
That's because you don't study until the\nnight before an exam! Cramming like that\nalways hurts your brain.

Sandy is correct. Exams are things
one must always face under perfect
circumstances. It would be good of
you to learn this, Becky.
Aaaaanyway, now that the exam's over,\nwhy don't we talk about something FUN?
I don't believe she's learned a thing.
It's your birthday soon, right, Cat?
We should put a party together for you!
I appreciate the sentiment, but I fear\nI am going to be quite busy.
I told you she'd say no, Becky.
But I want to celebrate with you...
What if we threw you a smaller,\nmore intimate party? Would that work?
I know you're helping out with all of your\nfather's mayoral duties, but surely you've\nearned a LITTLE time for fun.
Oh look, my escort is here! Looks like my\nproxy mayor work calls. Ta taaa, ladies!
(To be honest, a perfect woman such\nas me is barely bothered by the\ndemands of a busy schedule.)
(But I turn down birthday parties so I\ndon't have to feel like that again...)
Mommy said we have to give you a big\nparty 'cause you're the mayor's daughter!
(That birthday party was not about\ncelebrating me as a person at all,\nand the memory is still sour. But...)

(Oh, ENOUGH, Catherine! Get a grip!
How long have you known those two?
Have you ever seen even a hint of
ulterior motives from them?)
Sandy and Becky are my best friends,\nand they should not be made to suffer\nat the hands of my own cowardice!
I hope they are still in the plaza.
...just give her a present\nand call it good!
...Cat's rich enough to get\nwhatever she wants...
And just what is THAT supposed to mean?!
Oh yay! Does this mean you finished\nall your proxy mayor duties?
Spare me your churlish attempts at\ndistraction and answer my query!
What did you mean by what you just said?
Uh, did I even say something just now...?\nOh, RIGHT! The ＂rich＂ thing!
Well, since you're pretty bucks up and the\nmayor's daughter and all, we wanted—
To throw me a birthday party?
Becky. Shut up. You idiot.\nLook, Cat, it's not what you're—
I thought you were my true and bosom\ncompanions, but in the end you are no\nbetter than common lickspittles.
Cat, are you mad at us?
Listen to us, Catherine. Becky was—
Your words already came to my ears\nlouder than cannon fire.
You wish to throw me a birthday party\ndue to my wealth and standing!
Look, you're getting part of this,\nbut you're missing the REAL part.
You two sought to debase yourselves in\norder to curry my favor! Admit it!
Are you SERIOUSLY accusing us of that?!
Ugh, you are such a...PERSON sometimes!\nHere's a tip: Drop the deluded persecution\ncomplex for a second—you'll feel better.
Oh, if only this were a delusion!
I thought you two were different.\nTruly I did.

(I don't want to be in Quinbell anymore...
But where can I find a place where people
see me for who I am, as opposed to what
I have or can be used to gain?)
(Say, that's right! I could go to the people\nwho helped with the village festival!)

Right, that's everything! Take these
documents to the town hall and the
youth organization and let them know I
will be going away.
As you wish, young miss.\nBut where will you be going?
To learn from a prince.\nQuickly, now! Ready the carriage!
